&lt;!-- # Michael DeCrescenzo --&gt;

&lt;!-- ### Ph.D. Candidate, Political Science --&gt;

&lt;!-- ### I am a Ph.D. Candidate in Political Science at the University of Wisconsin--Madison. --&gt;

&lt;!-- I study U.S. politics and political methodology. --&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;i-study-u-s-elections-and-public-opinion-with-bayesian-methods&#34;&gt;I study U.S. elections and public opinion with Bayesian methods.&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My current projects deal with ideological representation in primary elections, party coalitions, and election administration. I have growing interests in model-driven measurement and Bayesian approaches to causal inference.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I employ computational methods throughout my work, most notably with statistical analysis (MCMC methods) and open-source project development.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;!-- Most of my teaching focuses experience focuses on mathematical, statistical, and software foundations for social science research methods. --&gt;

&lt;!-- My teaching experience covers research methods and American political behavior. Most of my teaching focuses on mathematical, statistical, and software foundations for social science research.  --&gt;

